textBeforeTable: 2015 Tour Dates Low price $33 High price $182 Average Price $112 Past 12 Months Find Tickets Sepultura Ticket Prices Sepultura Tickets - A Salve of Sepultura on the BrainThey weren't just traditional heavy metal, by any stretch. Originally focusing on 'death metal' with some hardcore thrashing vocals, you could hear inspirations of Metallica, Iron Maiden, and Anthrax in their work. Additionally, Brazilian culture made them stand out with the use of the ethnic drums and sounds of Brazil succinctly added in. Sepultura has the unique style that defines them as the quintessential heavy metal band on the genre. Schizophrenia following suit in 1987. Their first hit off the first album was a track entitled 'Troops of Doom.' Since then they had gained quite the following, particularly in Brazil itself. Morbid Visions and then Sepultura Tickets - A 'Rage Against the Machine' in BrazilThat is, however, a rather inaccurate comparison -- as there's no rap-metal element there. But the thrash is there, and you can hear it in their music, starting with their first LP Sepultura Tickets - The Brazilian Beasts UnchainedYou
